ZH: 他是个大手大脚的人，总是买很多不必要的东西。
EN: He is a big spender, always buying unnecessary things.

ZH: 她的大手大脚让她花光了所有的积蓄。
EN: Her lavish spending has depleted all her savings.

ZH: 我从小就被教育不要太大手大脚。
EN: I was taught from a young age not to be too extravagant.

ZH: 他的大手大脚让他经常陷入经济困境。
EN: His extravagant spending frequently lands him in financial trouble.

ZH: 她的大手大脚使她无法节约钱。
EN: Her spending habits make it difficult for her to save money.

ZH: 如果你一直大手大脚地花钱，迟早会遇到麻烦。
EN: If you keep spending recklessly, you will eventually run into trouble.

ZH: 他总是大手大脚地给女朋友买礼物。
EN: He always lavishly buys gifts for his girlfriend.

ZH: 我们应该谨慎花钱，不要太大手大脚。
EN: We should be cautious with our spending and not be too extravagant.

ZH: 她是那种大手大脚的女孩，永远不会缺少名牌服装。
EN: She is the kind of girl who splurges and never lacks designer clothes.

ZH: 他的大手大脚导致他的信用卡欠款不断增加。
EN: His extravagant spending has led to a constantly increasing credit card debt.

ZH: 我们应该从现在开始学会节俭，不要再大手大脚了。
EN: We should start being frugal from now on and avoid being extravagant.

ZH: 她的大手大脚让她很快就变得贫穷了。
EN: Her lavish spending quickly made her poor.

ZH: 这个国家的政府也是大手大脚，花钱超过了预算。
EN: The government of this country is also a big spender, spending beyond the budget.

ZH: 我很羡慕那些大手大脚的富人，随心所欲地花钱。
EN: I envy those wealthy spendthrifts who can spend freely.

ZH: 他的大手大脚让他的家庭遭受了巨大的经济压力。
EN: His extravagant spending has put immense financial pressure on his family.

ZH: 她是那种大手大脚的人，总是买最贵的东西。
EN: She is the kind of person who splurges on the most expensive things.

ZH: 他的大手大脚使他无法在急需之时支付账单。
EN: His lavish spending makes it difficult for him to pay bills when needed.

ZH: 如果你过于大手大脚，你的未来可能会受到影响。
EN: If you are too extravagant, your future may be affected.

ZH: 他的大手大脚让他陷入了债务的漩涡。
EN: His extravagant spending has plunged him into a whirlpool of debt.
